The paper deals with the computational complexity of a variant of the popular online puzzle game 2048, which involves finding a sequence of moves to reach a particular configuration from an initial configuration. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational complexity (cs.CC) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the complexity of the problem using reductions and algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), or computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-categories.
